Ukrainian Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba said that he is ready for fresh talks with his Russian counterpart Sergey Lavrov, the Ukrainian news outlet Ukrayinska Pravda reported Friday."I am ready to talk to him, I am ready to have a serious, substantive conversation with him," Kuleba was quoted as saying.Kuleba emphasized that the possible meeting should focus on finding solutions to the conflict between Ukraine and Russia.On March 10, Kuleba and Lavrov met in Turkey on the sidelines of an international forum in the presence of Turkish Foreign Minister Mevlut Cavusoglu.